MSI has revealed a pair of new mechanical keyboards, the Vigor GK80 and GK70. Both keyboards feature per-key RGB lighting, with support for MSIâ€™s Mystic Light software, and braided cables with gold-plated connectors. The Vigor GK80 is a full-sized keyboard which uses either Cherry MX Red or Speed Silver switches, and includes dedicated media keys and a detachable palm rest. The GK70 is a smaller, tenkeyless keyboard which sports either Cherry MX Speed Silver or Red switches, and a combination of metal and rubber keycaps. Both mechanical keyboards feature N-key rollover and Windows key lock, and will be available from March 2018. There is currently no pricing information available.      